    "created_at": "2015-10-30T04:08:19Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-30T04:08:19Z",
    "body": "From Chromium's source code is seems that they decided to only enable battery monitoring on Window:\n\n``` c++\n#if defined(OS_WIN)\n#include <windows.h>\n\n// Windows HiRes timers drain the battery faster so we need to know the battery\n// status.  This isn't true for other platforms.\n#define ENABLE_BATTERY_MONITORING 1\n#else\n#undef ENABLE_BATTERY_MONITORING\n#endif  // !OS_WIN\n```\n\nAnyway they implemented the battery monitoring by setting a 10s timer, so it is probably a good thing to not enable that.\n"
  },
