    "created_at": "2017-01-10T06:38:26Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-01-10T06:38:26Z",
    "body": "For anyone stumbling across this - we should definitely get macOS support for powerMonitor into Electron (anyone want to submit a PR?) In the meantime though, you can get battery / AC charger status from macOS with this shell command:\r\n\r\n```\r\npmset -g batt\r\n\r\nNow drawing from 'Battery Power'\r\n -InternalBattery-0 (id=3080291)\t66%; discharging; 4:20 remaining present: true\r\n```\r\nUnfortunately you'd need to poll, but doing it every 5 minutes or so probably isn't bad."
